				<span class="name">Dr. Zahed Sheikholeslami - Executive Dean</span>
				<span class="cv">Zahed was the Director of the project-based Learning Institute and the Director of Corporate Relations for the College of Engineering at the California Polytechnic State University (CalPoly).  Prior to joining CalPoly, Zahed was the Vice President of Business Development for Mikros Technologies in New Hampshire, USA.  Early in his career, Zahed was the Director of Marketing for 'Create', a research and development consulting firm based in New Hampshire, until 1992, when he joined a software start-up called Flomerics, Inc.  in Massachusetts.  Zahed was the President of Flomerics from 1993 to 2000, where under his leadership the company's revenue grew ten-fold.  In 2000 he left his position to start a new company, CoolingZone.  Zahed was the co-founder of Sharif University of Technology Association and was its president from 2004 to 2006. He is also the President of the International Association of Iranian Managers (I-AIM).  Over the past decade, Zahed has successfully conducted many workshops in Iran in strategic management and entrepreneurship.  Zahed received his BS Degree in Mechanical Engineering from Sharif University of Technology and earned a PhD from the University of Iowa in computational fluid dynamics.  He is IBS's Executive Dean and is based in Tehran. </span>
				<span class="name">Rouzbeh Pirouz (Chairman)</span>
				<span class="cv">Rouzbeh is an International Relations graduate of Stanford and Harvard Universities. Rouzbeh studied as a Rhodes Scholar at Oxford University, writing a doctoral thesis on Contemporary Civil Society Development in Iran. He co-founded and was Chief Executive Officer of a leading European technology firm, Mondus Ltd. In 2002, he founded Civility, and later created the Civility Programme in partnership with the Foreign Policy Centre. He is currently Senior Partner of Pelican Partners, a private equity and property investment firm based in London and is a member of the Board of Directors of the Iran Heritage Foundation.</span>
				<span class="name">Reza Moradi (Project Managing Director)</span>
				<span class="cv">Reza has a BSc and an MSc from Isfahan University of Technology in Engineering. He is the founder of the Iron and Steel Society of Iran and the founder of Iran's first technology incubator, Qadir. He also founded Sheikh Bahaee Technology Park in Isfahan. In addition, he was the Vice President for Executive Affairs of Isfahan Science & Technology town. He was also the Secretary of the 7th National Economic Development Congress, held in Iran to study the relations between government, industry and universities they pertain to economic development. He has taught several university level courses and is widely published in the field of Incubator and Science Park Management.</span>
				<span class="name">Roshanak Khalili-Dwyer</span>
				<span class="cv">Roshanak has a BA in East Asian Studies and Political Science from Connecticut College, holds a Master's Degree in International Relations from Columbia University and an MSc from the London Business School Sloan Fellowship Programme. She is advisor to the Board of Directors of Butane Industrial Group. She has further experience in finance through her seven-year tenure at Bankers Trust both in New York and London. Roshanak currently serves as director for the Institute for Family Business UK and is a member of the London Business School UK Regional Advisory Board. She is a member of the Board of Directors of the Iran Heritage Foundation.</span>
				<span class="name">Mahtab Hanjani</span>
